Traineeship Description
We are looking for an enthusiastic individual to join our engineering team. This role would suit for a recent graduate. This would provide a fantastic opportunity to gain valuable M&amp;E designing experience in plumbing &amp; Sanitary. The role would greatly complement candidate’s academic studies with exciting and interesting Designing project experience. They should possess for a mechanical engineering degree and be keen to gain some practical experience. This positon will report to the BIM Manager.
Specific Responsibilities
1. Follow up on Drawings and Designing Method.
2. Designing Engineer attends tender meetings and draw basic drawing as per BIM manager Advice.
3. Prepare Submission to Main Contractor for approval.
4. Amendment drawings issue has been follow up.
5. Follow up with Designing Department on M&amp;E (Pluming and Sanitary) shop drawings; involve in designing methods and approval submission.
Competencies Trainee will learn
1. To their intellectual and analytical abilities to further their development in the M&amp; E designing profession.
2. To identify how they can complement their formal training by self-help.
3. To develop a natural inquisitive sense and 'question' 'why' and 'how' things are done, with the aim of improving procedures and thus productivity.

Qualification
1.Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident;
2. Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); - Mechanical Engineering
3. Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.